The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Wednesday, October 02, 2002 				 ACU clean chit to meet
																								Colombo: The ICCs Anti-Corruption Unit (ACU) is satisfied with the purity of the just-concluded Champions Trophy, ICC chief executive Malcolm Speed said on Tuesday.																								ACU chief Paul Condon attended the two-day meeting of the ICC executive board here and reported on the tournament as well as security measures in general, Speed told reporters.																								Condon was pleased with what happened here. He said he had got great support and co-operation from the local officials, Speed said when asked if the ACU had found anything amiss during the meet. (PTI)
